verses.text_plain: Awake, awake; put on thy strength, O Zion; put on thy beautiful garments, O Jerusalem, the holy city: for henceforth there shall no more come into thee the uncircumcised and the unclean.
verses.verse_html: 1Awake, awake; put on thy strength, O Zion; put on thy beautiful garments, O Jerusalem, the holy city: for henceforth there shall no more come into thee the uncircumcised and the unclean.

tokens.text: for henceforth there shall no more

verses.text_plain: Shake thyself from the dust; arise, and sit down, O Jerusalem: loose thyself from the bands of thy neck, O captive daughter of Zion.
verses.verse_html: 2Shake thyself from the dust; arise, and sit down, O Jerusalem: loose thyself from the bands of thy neck, O captive daughter of Zion.

verses.text_plain: For thus saith the Lord, Ye have sold yourselves for nought; and ye shall be redeemed without money.
verses.verse_html: 3For thus saith the Lord, Ye have sold yourselves for nought; and ye shall be redeemed without money.

verses.text_plain: For thus saith the Lord God, My people went down aforetime into Egypt to sojourn there; and the Assyrian oppressed them without cause.
verses.verse_html: 4For thus saith the Lord God, My people went down aforetime into Egypt to sojourn there; and the Assyrian oppressed them without cause.

verses.text_plain: Now therefore, what have I here, saith the Lord, that my people is taken away for nought? they that rule over them make them to howl, saith the Lord; and my name continually every day is blasphemed.
verses.verse_html: 5Now therefore, what have I here, saith the Lord, that my people is taken away for nought? they that rule over them make them to howl, saith the Lord; and my name continually every day is blasphemed.

tokens.text: Now therefore, what have I here, saith
over them make them to howl

verses.text_plain: Therefore my people shall know my name: therefore they shall know in that day that I am he that doth speak: behold, it is I.
verses.verse_html: 6Therefore my people shall know my name: therefore they shall know in that day that I am he that doth speak: behold, it is I.

verses.text_plain: How beautiful upon the mountains are the feet of him that bringeth good tidings, that publisheth peace; that bringeth good tidings of good, that publisheth salvation; that saith unto Zion, Thy God reigneth!
verses.verse_html: 7How beautiful upon the mountains are the feet of him that bringeth good tidings, that publisheth peace; that bringeth good tidings of good, that publisheth salvation; that saith unto Zion, Thy God reigneth!

tokens.text: of him that bringeth good tidings

verses.text_plain: Thy watchmen shall lift up the voice; with the voice together shall they sing: for they shall see eye to eye, when the Lord shall bring again Zion.
verses.verse_html: 8Thy watchmen shall lift up the voice; with the voice together shall they sing: for they shall see eye to eye, when the Lord shall bring again Zion.

verses.text_plain: Break forth into joy, sing together, ye waste places of Jerusalem: for the Lord hath comforted his people, he hath redeemed Jerusalem.
verses.verse_html: 9Break forth into joy, sing together, ye waste places of Jerusalem: for the Lord hath comforted his people, he hath redeemed Jerusalem.

verses.text_plain: The Lord hath made bare his holy arm in the eyes of all the nations; and all the ends of the earth shall see the salvation of our God.
verses.verse_html: 10The Lord hath made bare his holy arm in the eyes of all the nations; and all the ends of the earth shall see the salvation of our God.

verses.text_plain: Depart ye, depart ye, go ye out from thence, touch no unclean thing; go ye out of the midst of her; be ye clean, that bear the vessels of the Lord.
verses.verse_html: 11Depart ye, depart ye, go ye out from thence, touch no unclean thing; go ye out of the midst of her; be ye clean, that bear the vessels of the Lord.

verses.text_plain: For ye shall not go out with haste, nor go by flight: for the Lord will go before you; and the God of Israel will be your rereward.
verses.verse_html:
12For ye shall not go out with haste, nor go by flight: for the Lord will go before you; and the God of Israel will be your rereward.
 be: Heb. gather you up

tokens.text: For ye shall not go out

footnotes.body_html: be: Heb. gather you up

verses.text_plain: Behold, my servant shall deal prudently, he shall be exalted and extolled, and be very high.
verses.verse_html:
13Behold, my servant shall deal prudently, he shall be exalted and extolled, and be very high.
 deal: or, prosper

verses.text_plain: As many were astonied at thee; his visage was so marred more than any man, and his form more than the sons of men:
verses.verse_html: 14As many were astonied at thee; his visage was so marred more than any man, and his form more than the sons of men:

verses.text_plain: So shall he sprinkle many nations; the kings shall shut their mouths at him: for that which had not been told them shall they see; and that which they had not heard shall they consider.
verses.verse_html: 15So shall he sprinkle many nations; the kings shall shut their mouths at him: for that which had not been told them shall they see; and that which they had not heard shall they consider.
